======<br>
<br>
you have wrote &quot;This will make a paladin and cleric pair the best healing pair in the game, but not so much more than a cleric alone so that a paladin is required to augment a cleric&quot;<br>
<br>
my answer:<br>
<br>
pallys wont be the &quot;best healng pair&quot; with a cleric because torpor / chloroblast / natures touch is better than any kind of stackable dot heal for 250 dmg a pally could ever do.<br>
<br>
Pallys shouldnt even be worrying about healing as there are 3 classes other than them that can do it soooooo much better, you should be concentrating on getting your tanking ability improved.<br>
<br>
<br>
why the f**k would you want a lamet 250 dmg heal dot when you could have celestial healing / celestial elixir / torpor / cleric group heals<br>
<br>
250 is not much dmg to give back, and a dot is just gonna be even worse and even if it took 20 seconds for the dot to work thats 12.5 dmg a second, pointless ?<br>
<br>
<br>
Get it ? <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umaani.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Maani</A> at: 7/24/01 4:28:14 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ueliezar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Eliezar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(7/24/01 4:37:24 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Carving Out A UNIQUE End Game Paladin Role</span><hr size=1> What would turn a paladin from being a fill in to a primary player in many fights?<br>
<br>
Its not upping damage because even with 90 percent of a warriors damage you won't do that much in a raid situation.<br>
<br>
Fighting velious uber mobs the warriors either use defensive or precision so that they massively out tank a paladin OR easily out damage a paladin.  Now in Kunark uber mob type fights the warriors can use their burn discs to have a nice damage burst and make paladins second class melees as well.<br>
<br>
I think the one thing that could really make paladins have a role of importance in some end game encounters would be to make paladins 55+ immune to fear.  Whether it is a 3 min disc or full immunity I could care less but it would make sense.<br>
<br>
Suddenly the paladin is the tank against Zlandicar, Klandicar, Talendor, etc.  I wouldn't find this unbalancing because on my server there are only 1 or 2 paladins per end game guild.  It would however make paladins have a niche to fill in the end game.  <br>
<br>
If the paladin was going to get anything spellwise I think a group Yaulp would be pretty interesting.<br>
<br>
<br>
