<br>
The 60th druid spell sucks frankly.  I know more than a few druids that use chloroblast over it because chloroblast might land on the enchanter that gets aggro, but nature's touch probably won't.  They are equally efficient as well.  Druids really deserve a fire lure that is about 15 percent weaker than a wizards best fire lure OR they deserve to have Nature's Touch be changed to 400mana 1600hps in 10 seconds.  The current spell is just a joke.  Give them something that is useful.<br>
<br>
Shaman are better healers than druids (for a few levels, 24-33 and 60th) because they don't have an offensive role on raids.  Druids can actually land fire DDs for full damage on a lot of end game mobs (Dain, Statue of Rallos Zek come to mind) while shamen have little or no offensive role on raids.<br>
<br>
Eliezar<br>
